      "writtenOn": "2026-05-14T16:25:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "why does the move assignment operator call abandon_if_unreplied but the move construction operator doesn\u0027t? These should generally symmetric.",
      "revId": "acf07bc2f5d707a9a3dce6d7096801b038cc34e7",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "23ac6840_01e821a5",
        "filename": "include/sdbusplus/asio/object_server.hpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 326,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002885
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-15T13:17:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The asymmetry is intentional. In move-construction `*this` is being created and `request_` is directly initialized from `other.request_` in the mem-init list. So there is no prior request on `*this` to abandon.\nHowever, in the move-assignment, `*this` already exists and may hold a live un-replied request. Calling `abandon_if_unreplied()` first sends `-EIO` to that original caller before we overwrite(otherwise they will time out).",
      "parentUuid": "0b283d1f_df386a16",
      "revId": "acf07bc2f5d707a9a3dce6d7096801b038cc34e7",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f6ac908e_2b103650",
        "filename": "include/sdbusplus/asio/object_server.hpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 335,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002504
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-14T16:25:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is it safe to call this twice?",
      "revId": "acf07bc2f5d707a9a3dce6d7096801b038cc34e7",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "40249274_710bc190",
        "filename": "include/sdbusplus/asio/object_server.hpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 335,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002885
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-05-15T13:17:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think yes because `abandon_if_unreplied()` is idempotent.\nIt guards on `if (replied_ || ~request_) return;` initially and set `replied_ \u003d true` at the end, so any second call will be short-circuited at the guard.",
      "parentUuid": "f6ac908e_2b103650",
      "revId": "acf07bc2f5d707a9a3dce6d7096801b038cc34e7",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
